🔹 Step 1: Create AWS Resources
Launch EC2 instance
Create S3 bucket (projectbucketfinops)

👉 These are the resources you monitor

🔹 Step 2: Create DynamoDB Table
Service: DynamoDB
Table name: FinOpsProject

Attributes:

Resource ID
Action
Timestamp

👉 Stores all actions done by the system

🔹 Step 3: Create SNS Topic
Service: Amazon SNS
Topic name: finops-alerts

Add subscription:

Protocol: Email
Enter your email → confirm

👉 Used to send:

Cost alerts
Reports
Suggestions
🔹 Step 4: Create Lambda Function
Service: AWS Lambda
Name: finops-governance-engine
Runtime: Python

👉 This is the main processing unit

🔹 Step 5: Write Lambda Logic

Inside Lambda, implement:

Check EC2 instances
Stop idle instances
Read S3 usage
Analyze cost using Cost Explorer
Generate recommendations
Store logs in DynamoDB
Send alerts using SNS

👉 This step handles:

EC2 auto-stop
S3 analysis
Cost checking
Recommendations
🔹 Step 6: Enable Cost Explorer
Open AWS Cost Explorer
Enable it

👉 Used to:

Check service-wise cost
Detect high usage
🔹 Step 7: Create EventBridge Rule
Service: Amazon EventBridge
Create rule (Scheduled)

Example:

Run every day / every hour

👉 Automates the execution

🔹 Step 8: Connect EventBridge to Lambda
Select your Lambda as target

👉 Now Lambda runs automatically

🔹 Step 9: System Execution Flow

👉
EventBridge triggers Lambda

Lambda:

Checks EC2 → stops unused
Reads S3 usage
Gets cost data
Stores logs in DynamoDB
Sends alerts using SNS
🔹 Step 10: Verify Output

Check:

EC2 stopped if unused ✅
Logs in DynamoDB ✅
Email alerts received ✅
🔹 Step 11: Final Result
Reduced cloud cost 💸
Automated monitoring
Smart resource control
